******************************* NEWS FOR 2026-07-01 ****************************

Welcome to the v0.4 release!

This is the fourth beta release of Pascal-P6.

What has been done since the v0.3 release:

Native code generation (pgen):

* AMD64 SysV ABI parameter passing: register and overflow parameters with
caller cleanup, making Pascal and C calls fully interoperable at the ABI
level.

* DWARF debug information: types, subranges, file types, and CFI backtraces.
Compiled Pascaline programs are now debuggable in GDB.

* Correctly rounded real to decimal conversion, using an exact big-integer
converter in place of the power-of-ten approximation.

The Petit-Ami I/O stack bound to Pascaline:

* Full library bindings for services, terminal, graphics, widgets, sound and
network, statically linked.

* Seven graphical games (chess, backgammon, conquest, checkers, breakout,
defenders and pong) written as end to end validation of the graphics, sound
and widget bindings, installed as ready to run binaries.

Interpreter family expansion:

* Terminal and graphics hosted flavors of every interpreter: pint/pintt/pintg,
pmach/pmacht/pmachg and cmach/cmacht/cmachg.

* Sound and network are standard in all interpreter flavors, and cmach hosts
the complete external set with zero stubs.

New tools:

* pc, the Pascaline compile driver: module auto-detection, library linking,
and package mode, which produces stand-alone executables with an embedded
interpreter from prebuilt objects.

* p2c, a Pascal to C translator, capable of compiling the ISO 7185 PAT
including nested procedures, variant records, with statements, goto/setjmp
and typed file I/O.

* pasdoc, an HTML documentation generator with source views, cross links and
sidebar navigation.

* pasfmt, a Pascaline source formatter.

* passym, a symbol server powering the editor tooling.

IDE support:

* VSCode extension: syntax highlighting, language server (completion, hover,
go to definition, find references), and a debug adapter driving pint with
breakpoints and a debug REPL.

Conformance and testing:

* ISO 7185 conformance fixes (negative mod, file-of-record writes) plus
expanded PAT context test batteries and the iso7185prt rejectance suite.

* Parallel regression: all five backend models run concurrently.

* The spew fuzzer hardens pcom against crash classes; the outbound test
verifies a fresh repository clone runs the full regression with no build
step.

Distribution:

* create_user builds a runtime-only user distribution (binaries, libraries
and games; no sources, no self-rebuild), including source-free package mode.

* configure/update host tree system for per-configuration restore and
refresh.

BASIC:

* The BASIC interpreter gained new statements, command line parsing, nested
procedures, a test suite, and a playable chess demo.

Compiler front end (pcom):

* Steady fixes: string ABI for filename arguments, variant record safety,
error handling refactor and option handling, plus internal "theops"
documentation chapters for the tools.

Pascaline features not implemented in Pascal-P6 v0.4:

* 64 bit Linux is the only supported version. At this time, only 64 bit Linux is
tested and supported.

That's it! Enjoy playing around with the system.

Scott Franco
San Jose, CA

